HEADWORD: Dry goods
<hw>Dry" goods`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A commercial name for textile
fabrics, cottons, woolens, linen, silks, laces, etc., -- in distinction
from <xex>groceries</xex>.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drying</ent>⟦br⟧
